column2: 1. Data in these tables were extracted from the National Immunisation Management Service on 1st June 2021.
2. Note these figures may be updated as more information becomes available from local systems.
3. Only records with a vaccination date between 8th December 2020 to 30th May 2021 have been included.
4. The sum of MSOAs will not equal the England total. This is due to a number of individuals vaccinated in England with a registered address in Scotland or Wales or where their address is unknown.

5. These figures include all individuals identified in the relevant age bands. For example 80+ includes all people who have been vaccinated who are aged 80+ and does not exclude those who are in a higher priortiy group for vaccination as set out by the Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation (i.e. care home residents). Individuals aged under 30 may have been vaccinated as part of a higher priority group, for example, if they are clinically extremely vulnerable or in an at risk group.
6. The sum of the age groups across doses will not equal the cumulative total. This is due to a number of individuals with an unknown age.
